------------------------------------------------

Language Models process text in chunks called tokens.
Common words are often single tokens, while complex
words or specific code syntax might be split up.

For example:
- "apple" is 1 token.
- "const" is 1 token.
- "12345" might be 1-3 tokens depending on context.

